Thanks for all of the work that you've done on flyway! I've been looking forward to all of the cool new features in Flyway 4.0 and I've been playing around with the latest version of the code to see how I might be able to use it in the future. 

I'm faced with a situation where it would be useful to have the ability to always apply one or more repeatable migrations before any versioned migrations so that the versioned migrations can all make use of a number of version controlled functions/stored procedures.

Allowing users to supply a custom MigrationInfo comparator that would only be used to compare repeatable migrations would make it possible to run repeatable migrations in any desired order. Just as an example, repeatable migrations in a "procedures" subdirectory could always be run before all other migrations, while repeatable migrations in a "views" subdirectory could always be run after all other migrations, etc.

I have a barebones implementation of this feature in [this fork](https://github.com/ericparton/flyway/commit/a72fc4968babdd1db1337b8d61ef0b2c0fb9da45), and I would be happy to submit a pull request after adding tests and the plugin configurations if you think that this would be a worthwhile contribution.

Thanks
